explanation:
## Why Asked
Tests ability to verify end-to-end functionality across API and database layers.

## Key Concepts
- HTTP status codes and response validation
- Database transaction verification
- Test data setup and cleanup
- Mocking external dependencies

## Code Example
```
describe('POST /users', () => {
  it('should create user and save to database', async () => {
    const userData = { name: 'John', email: 'john@test.com' };
    const response = await request(app)
      .post('/users')
      .send(userData);

    expect(response.status).toBe(201);
    expect(response.body.name).toBe(userData.name);

    const dbUser = await db.users.findById(response.body.id);
    expect(dbUser.email).toBe(userData.email);
  });
});
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle test data isolation?
- When would you mock the database?
- How do you test error scenarios?
